						               													<description>Story and goal&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All children are rooting in the leaves. Because under the colorful foliage  many animals have hidden - also fruits and cones are below it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn adds an extra sheet with a new theme mixed on the  bottom among the others.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Who finds it the first to root?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Preparation:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a) Sort out the leaves with pictures and put them in the bag.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The other leaves are distributed on the &amp;quot;forest floor&amp;quot; in the box bottom. Then you put the coins next to the Box ready.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The youngest player starts, then it goes clockwise continue.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you are the youngest child, take the fabric bag and take out a sheet without  looking into it. Look at the motive on the underside secret, without the others can see.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Remember this motif and hide it under the leaves in the box  while the other players turn around.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you have hidden the sheet, your teammates - with one hand - dig in the pile of foliage, just for this new one&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To search motive. The leaves may be opened and closed&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Be careful, but be careful when digging: Leaves must remain in the box.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Anyone who thinks they have found the new motive they are looking for calls the name of  the animal or the fruit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Was it correct, the player may take a gold coin. The sheet comes back in the box, in such a way that the picture is hidden.&amp;#10;     If it is wrong, the other players may (only) continue to dig,&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;until one  finds the right motive and gets a gold coin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of the game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As soon as the last motive has been found in the heap of leaves and given the correct name, the game is over. Who has collected the most gold coins, wins the game! If two or more players have the same number of coins, they win together.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Have fun digging, grumbling, rustling and finding!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
